{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Val}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

The 'Val attribute is defined for all discrete types. It is a function returning that value of the base type of S having the argument's position number; the prefix S must be a subtype name. (Any specific integer type is implicitly converted to ''universal_integer''.)

 function S'Val (Arg: universal_integer) return S'Base;

If no value of the type of S has the position number Arg, the Constraint_Error [[Ada Programming/Exceptions|exception]] is raised.

Note that representation clauses do not affect position numbering. Whatever underlying value the enumerated value has, the position number will remain the same.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/--|Declare a discrete type; the compiler will assign the internal representation as 0 .. 2}}
 {{Ada/--|identical to the position numbers.}}
 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Enum1, Enum2, Enum3);

 {{Ada/--|Declare a discrete type and explicitly set the internal representation.}}
 {{Ada/--|Note that the position numbers are still 0 .. 2.}}
 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Other_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Value1, Value2, Value3);
 {{Ada/kw|for}} My_Other_Enum {{Ada/kw|use}} (Value1 => 2, Value2 => 4, Value3 => 6);

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Val(0) = Enum1);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Val(1) = Enum2);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Val(2) = Enum3);  {{Ada/--|OK}}

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(0) = Value1);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(1) = Value2);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(2) = Value3);  {{Ada/--|OK}}

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Val(3)       = Enum3);  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(2) = Value1); {{Ada/--|Wrong}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(4) = Value2); {{Ada/--|Wrong}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Other_Enum'Val(6) = Value3); {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

The internal representation can only be queried via Unchecked_Conversion.

== See also ==

The inverse of the 'Val attribute is 'Pos.

