{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Last}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

<code>X'{{Ada/attribute|Last}}</code>, where <code>X</code> is any [[ada Programming/Subtypes|scalar subtype]] (for example integer, enumerated, real), is an [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] that represents the last value (upper bound) in the range of <code>X</code>.

<code>A'{{Ada/attribute|Last}}</code>, where <code>A</code> is an array, denotes the last index value. For more-dimensional arrays, <code>A'{{Ada/attribute|Last(N)}}</code> denotes the last index value of the Nth dimension (N must be static).

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Enum1, Enum2, Enum3);
 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Int  {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|range}} -1 .. 5;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Last = Enum3);  {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Int'Last  = 5);      {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Int'Last  = 4);      {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong!}}

