{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Succ}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Succ(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any discrete type and Y is a value of that type. This attribute represents the discrete value that has a position number of one greater than the input parameter.

The returned discrete value type is the base type of discrete type. If the input parameter is the {{Ada/attribute|Last}} value of the discrete type, then a CONSTRAINT_ERROR [[Ada Programming/Exceptions|exception]] will be raised.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Enum1, Enum2, Enum3);
 ...
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Succ(Enum2) = Enum3);   {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Succ(Enum3) = Enum1);   {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong}}

